[2026-03-19T08:32:36.885Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J2vHZQ8TdfrzHZF7PqhXgd","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a final summary of the exploration:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI have thoroughly explored the personas-cloud codebase. Here's my detailed findings:\n\n### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n**Project Type:** Node.js/TypeScript monorepo with three packages (DAC Cloud - Distributed Agent Computation)\n\n**Workspace Structure:**\n```\nC:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\.claude\\worktrees\\reactive-gathering-parrot\\\n├── packages/\n│   ├── orchestrator/     (Main API server & job scheduler)\n│   ├── worker/          (Execution agent connecting to orchestrator)\n│   └── shared/          (Shared types, crypto, protocol definitions)\n├── package.json         (Root workspace config)\n├── tsconfig.base.json   (Base TypeScript config)\n└── .env.example         (Configuration template)\n```\n\n### 2. DATABASE SCHEMA (Locations: `/packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts` - Lines 66-195)\n\n**Key Tables:**\n- **persona_executions** (Lines 171-192): Stores execution records with fields: id, project_id, persona_id, trigger_id, use_case_id, status, input_data, output_data, claude_session_id, model_used, input_tokens, output_tokens, cost_usd, error_message, duration_ms, retry_of_execution_id, retry_count, started_at, completed_at, created_at\n  \n- **persona_events** (Lines 129-142): Stores events with: id, project_id, event_type, source_type, source_id, target_persona_id, payload, status, error_message, processed_at, use_case_id, created_at\n\n- **persona_event_subscriptions** (Lines 145-155): Event subscriptions for personas\n- **persona_triggers** (Lines 157-169): Trigger definitions (manual, schedule, polling, webhook, chain)\n- **persona_credentials** (Lines 109-121): Encrypted credentials storage\n- **persona_credential_links** (Lines 123-127): Links personas to credentials\n- **persona_tools** (Lines 103-107): Links personas to tool definitions\n- **persona_tool_definitions** (Lines 88-101): Tool catalog\n- **personas** (Lines 67-86): Core persona definitions\n\n**Database Init:** SQLite with better-sqlite3, WAL mode, foreign key constraints enabled\n**Location:** `/packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts` lines 18-27\n\n### 3. EXISTING RETENTION-RELATED CODE\n**Limited/None Currently:** Search results show cleanup only exists for:\n- **Worker execution cleanup** (`/packages/worker/src/cleanup.ts`): Clears temporary directories and environment variables after execution completes\n  - Functions: `clearEnvVars()`, `cleanupTempDir()`, `createTempDir()`\n  - This is for per-execution cleanup, NOT data retention\n\n**No production data retention/purge logic found** - this is a gap to be filled\n\n### 4. METRICS & LOGGING PATTERNS\n**Logging Framework:** `pino` (pinpoint logging library)\n\n**Locations with Logging:**\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/index.ts`: Main entry point, periodic status logging (Lines 100-112)\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts`: Database operations logging\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts`: Event processing logs with structured context\n- `/packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts`: Execution dispatch and output handling\n- `/packages/worker/src/index.ts`: Worker lifecycle logs\n\n**Logging Pattern:** Structured logs with context objects: \n```typescript\nlogger.info({ key1: value1, key2: value2 }, 'Message')\n```\n\n**Status/Health Endpoint:** `/health` (GET, unauthenticated)\n- **Location:** `/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` lines 38-41, 473-482\n- **Response:** `{ status: 'ok', workers: {...}, hasSubscription: bool, timestamp: number }`\n\n### 5. SCHEDULED JOBS/CRON PATTERNS\n**Event Processor** (`/packages/orchestrator/src/eventProcessor.ts`):\n- Runs every 2 seconds (configurable, default 2000ms)\n- Function: `startEventProcessor()` lines 16-31\n- Processes pending events (limit 50 per tick) and dispatches to matching personas\n- Uses database for state persistence\n\n**Trigger Scheduler** (`/packages/orchestrator/src/triggerScheduler.ts`):\n- Runs every 5 seconds (configurable, default 5000ms)\n- Function: `startTriggerScheduler()` lines 12-26\n- Evaluates \"due\" triggers (scheduled, polling, webhook, chain)\n- Computes next trigger time using simple cron patterns: \"every Xs/m/h/d\"\n- Note: TODO to add full cron-parser support (Line 123)\n\n**OAuth Token Refresh Loop** (`/packages/orchestrator/src/index.ts`):\n- Refreshes every 30 minutes\n- Location: Lines 91-98\n\n**Status Logging Loop** (`/packages/orchestrator/src/index.ts`):\n- Logs worker counts and queue status every 60 seconds\n- Location: Lines 100-112\n\n### 6. CONFIGURATION & ENVIRONMENT\n**Orchestrator Config** (`/packages/orchestrator/src/config.ts`):\n- masterKey, claudeToken (optional), teamApiKey, workerToken\n- kafkaBrokers, kafkaUsername, kafkaPassword, kafkaEnabled\n- supabaseJwtSecret (optional)\n- wsPort (default 8443), httpPort (default 3001)\n\n**Worker Config** (`/packages/worker/src/config.ts`):\n- orchestratorUrl, workerToken, workerId (auto-generated if absent)\n\n**No retention/purge configuration found** - needs to be added\n\n### 7. HTTP API ENDPOINTS\n**Public (Unauthenticated):**\n- `GET /health` - Health check\n\n**Authenticated:**\n- `POST /api/oauth/*` - OAuth flow endpoints\n- `POST /api/token` - Direct token injection\n- `GET /api/personas` - List personas\n- `POST /api/personas` - Create persona\n- `GET /api/personas/{id}` - Get persona details\n- `GET /api/events` - List events with filtering\n- `POST /api/events` - Publish event\n- `PUT /api/events/{id}` - Update event status\n- `GET /api/executions` - List executions\n- `POST /api/execute` - Submit execution\n- `POST /api/executions/{id}/cancel` - Cancel execution\n- `GET /api/executions/{id}` - Get execution output\n- **Admin-only:** `/api/admin/users`, `/api/admin/personas`, `/api/admin/executions`\n\n**Location:** `/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts`\n\n### 8. AUTHENTICATION & AUTHORIZATION\n**Dual Auth System** (`/packages/orchestrator/src/auth.ts`):\n- API Key (Bearer token) - required always\n- Optional Supabase JWT (x-user-token header) - for user/project isolation\n- Falls back to admin context if JWT auth disabled\n- Project scoping: admin sees all, users see own project only\n\n### 9. EXECUTION FLOW\n**Dispatcher** (`/packages/orchestrator/src/dispatcher.ts`):\n- Queues execution requests\n- Assigns to available workers via WebSocket\n- Tracks active executions in-memory for real-time streaming\n- Persists to database and Kafka\n- Cleans up active execution tracking after 30 seconds of completion\n\n**Worker Pool** (`/packages/orchestrator/src/workerPool.ts`):\n- WebSocket server for workers\n- Tracks worker status and capacity\n- Routes messages (stdout, stderr, complete, events) back to dispatcher\n\n**Worker Execution** (`/packages/worker/src/executor.ts`):\n- Spawns Claude CLI as subprocess\n- Captures stdout/stderr with line buffering\n- Detects persona events in output\n- Sends heartbeats and completion messages back\n- Cleans up temp directories and env vars after execution\n\n### 10. MISSING/GAPS (Retention Focus)\n**No existing retention configuration found for:**\n- Execution retention window/TTL\n- Event retention window/TTL  \n- Data purge/cleanup jobs\n- Configurable retention policies\n- Metrics for data size/cleanup\n\n**This is the primary area for enhancement:**\n- Need to add retention config to orchestrator config\n- Need scheduled purge job for old executions/events\n- Need metrics collection for retention monitoring\n- Should add configurable retention windows per project or globally\n\n---\n\n**Key File Locations Summary:**\n- Database schema & operations: `/packages/orchestrator/src/db.ts` (738 lines)\n- HTTP API endpoints: `/packages/orchestrator/src/httpApi.ts` (500+ lines)\n- Con